fields.description:
Following [Configuring remote agent capabilities using bamboo-capabilities.properties|https://confluence.atlassian.com/x/sQM_EQ]:
# created the following {color:blue}bamboo-capabilities.properties{color}
{noformat}
my.ok.capability=ok
my.no.value=
=nokey
did.get.here=unsure
{noformat}
# started Bamboo remote agent
{code}
INFO   | jvm 1    | 2018/06/14 11:36:20 | 2018-06-14 11:36:20,732 INFO [AgentRunnerThread] [DefaultAgentCapabilityManagerImpl] Default agent capabilities loaded from bamboo-capabilities.properties
{code}
# reviewing agent's capabilities
 !remote.agent.capability.png|thumbnail! 
# from Bamboo's UI, capability cannot be created without a Key
 !ui.custom.capability.png|thumbnail!

/opt/bamboo-elastic-agent/bin/getCustomData.bat
returns a ClassNotFoundException.

 !image.png|thumbnail! 

The .bat needs to be changed to point to the absolute path of the .jar file.

{code}
@echo off

java -cp C:\opt\bamboo-elastic-agent\bin\atlassian-bamboo-agent-elastic-installer.jar com.atlassian.bamboo.agent.elastic.metadata.RetrieveMetaData %1 %2
{code}

According to our official documentation ([Bamboo Upgrade Guide|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/BAMBOO0604/Bamboo+upgrade+guide]), Bamboo's upgrade should work as:
{quote}
When upgrading from Bamboo 4.0 and later, you can upgrade directly to the latest version of Bamboo:
4.0+  >> LATEST
{quote}
However, according to [Upgrade task 4408 fails with: "java.sql.SQLException: ORA-22859: invalid modification of columns"|https://confluence.atlassian.com/x/nhGUO] when upgrading Oracle's database (_from 11g to 12c_), an intermediate Bamboo version (_e.g. v5.11_) is required.
